               Twenty-two cases with living plants were forwarded to the neighboring colonies or to more distant countries, and nineteen have been received as donations or in exchange from the Botanical Gardens of Auckland, Kew, Adelaide, Brisbane, Buitenzorg, Hobarton, and from Messrs. I. Bailey, Adelaide;

J. Bailey?
                F. Bailey, Wellington; F. Ferguson, Camden; Captain Kreeft, Wellington; Messrs. Shepherd, Sydney; and D. Wilkinson, Wellington. Other importations were effected by purchase.
